*   The Experiment Describer: 'What if we changed this variable?'
*   Concept Mapping: how Light connects to the Human Eye, atoms to reactions

### CLASS 9–12
*   Study Plan Prompt: input exam, date, hours, strong/weak subjects → week-by-week plan
*   Diagnostic assessment with AI: classify topics into Mastered / Needs Practice / Not Started
*   Spaced repetition scheduling: AI-generated revision calendar at optimal intervals
*   The Weekly Review Ritual: every Sunday, 15 mins with Claude to adjust your plan

# Session 6 | Olympiad Prep / AI for Maths & Quantitative Subjects
## Pattern recognition & unlimited practice

### CLASS 6–8
*   School vs. Olympiad: memory vs. application and creative thinking
*   Olympiad-specific strategies: NSO, IMO, NTSE, IEO — what each one tests
*   Pattern Recognition Technique: 'What patterns do you see in these 10 questions?'
*   Building your Olympiad Toolkit: trick types, high-frequency topics, 3-month schedule

### CLASS 9–12
*   Math-specific prompting: fractions, integrals, matrices in text
*   Unlimited practice: 'Generate 10 JEE Mains integration problems, increasing difficulty'
*   Derivation & proof assistance: hints only, not full proofs
*   CA Accountancy with AI: journal entries, ledger, ratio analysis, financial statements

# Session 7 | Building Your Study Plan / AI for Science Subjects
## Personalised study system | Physics, Chemistry & Biology

### CLASS 6–8
*   Study Plan Prompt with real exam dates, daily hours, strong vs. weak subjects
*   Spaced repetition as the Memory Staircase: Day 1 → 2 → 5 → 14 → 30
*   The Balanced Week: homework + AI study + Olympiad practice + revision + rest
*   The Sunday Review: 10 mins with Claude to adjust next week's plan

### CLASS 9–12
*   Physics with AI: describe setups in text, dimensional analysis, thought experiments
*   Chemistry with AI: reaction mechanisms step by step, exception lists, inorganic comparison tables
*   NCERT Deep Dive for NEET: 'Take this paragraph and create 5 MCQs from these exact lines'
*   NEET strategy: 90%+ of questions come from NCERT — AI helps extract every testable line

# Session 8 | Test Yourself Like a Topper / AI-Powered Mock Tests
## Custom tests, error analysis, and exam strategy

### CLASS 6–8
*   AI Test Generator: chapter-wise, Olympiad-style, mixed revision, and weak-spot tests
*   The Error Detective: wrong answer → what concept am I missing → what to study to fix this
*   Teach Your Mistakes Method: explain why the correct answer is correct
*   Timed practice: 2-minute rule, mark and move on

### CLASS 9–12
*   Generating mock tests matching JEE Mains (90Q), NEET (200Q), CA paper formats
*   Post-Test Analysis Protocol: accuracy breakdown, silly vs. conceptual errors, predicted score
*   Exam strategy optimisation: which section first, time per question, negative marking strategy
*   Previous year paper analysis: topic frequency heatmap, predicted high-probability topics

