# Content Creation & UX Writing *Brand Storyteller · UX Writer · Content Strategist*

## Why it fits | Pathway in India | Can grow into

India's digital economy targets $1 trillion by 2030. Every brand needs content, but few creators combine creativity with strong verbal ability (80%). UX Writing — writing for apps and digital products — is an emerging high-paying niche with very few trained professionals in India today. Her Enterprising interest (53%) means she can eventually lead these functions.

*BA English / Mass Comm. → Portfolio from Class 11 → UX Writing certifications*

Content Director · Brand Voice Consultant · Content Agency Founder

# Social Entrepreneurship & Impact Sector *Programme Manager · CSR Lead · NGO Director*

## Why it fits | Pathway in India | Can grow into

India's development sector is professionalising fast and recruiting creative, articulate graduates. Fellowships like Teach for India and Young India Fellowship are established stepping stones. Her profile — creative, empathetic, organised, 100% socially motivated — is exactly what the sector seeks. This is not a compromise career; it is a growth career with real leadership paths.

*BA Liberal Arts / Sociology → Fellowship (TFI · YIF) → MBA Social Entrepreneurship*

Impact Director · Social Enterprise Founder · Policy Advisor · UN Sector Roles

# Law — Social Justice Focus (CLAT) *Human Rights · Environmental · Child Rights Advocate*

## Why it fits | Pathway in India | Can grow into

Law scores in the assessment are moderate (41%), but we include this because Adwitiya's Creativity (100%) + Social Service (100%) make Social Justice Law genuinely meaningful — not just academically sound. Lawyers who combine empathy with rigour are in demand at NGOs, policy institutes, and international organisations. Her English (80%) and Logical Ability (80%) make CLAT achievable. We suggest treating this as one of three parallel options to explore — not the only path, but one worth an honest conversation.

*Arts stream → CLAT prep 2 yrs → NALSAR · Jindal Global Law School · NLU Delhi*

Human Rights Lawyer · Public Interest Litigator · Policy Researcher · NGO Legal Counsel

