Law scores in the assessment are moderate (41%), but we include this because Adwitiya's Creativity (100%) + Social Service (100%) make Social Justice Law genuinely meaningful — not just academically sound. Lawyers who combine empathy with rigour are in demand at NGOs, policy institutes, and international organisations. Her English (80%) and Logical Ability (80%) make CLAT achievable. We suggest treating this as one of three parallel options to explore — not the only path, but one worth an honest conversation.

